ffic safety.</p>\n<h2>Challenges and Considerations</h2>\n<p>While the implementation of mitigation measures shows promise, several challenges remain. Funding for infrastructure projects like wildlife crossings is limited and requires coordination between multiple agencies. Additionally, elk behavior is inherently unpredictable, and complete elimination of collision risks is unlikely.</p>\n<p>Balancing the interests of wildlife preservation with public safety demands ongoing monitoring and adaptive management. Authorities must remain vigilant in assessing the effectiveness of interventions and flexible in responding to changing ecological or traffic conditions.</p>\n<p>The elk herd Millcreek traffic concerns symbolize a broader challenge faced by many communities where expanding human development intersects with natural habitats. Finding sustainable solutions will necessitate collaboration among wildlife biologists, urban planners, transportation officials, and the public to ensure both safe roads and thriving elk populations.</p>",
